description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Based at Albany House &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;(on the site of Kingsway Hospital, Derby) &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An opening has become available for a Service Manager to join our Derby City Crisis team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a Band 7 Service Manager to join our team based at Kingsway Hospital, Derby.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Crisis and Home Treatment service runs 24 hours/ day across a 7 day week, 365 days per year.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be required to work between the hours of 9-5, Monday to Friday, with some level of flexibility, as required, to meet the needs of the service and the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This well established, multi-disciplinary team offers a high quality assessment and home treatment service as an alternative to hospital admission, to individuals experiencing acute mental health crises.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working in partnership with patients, families and existing service providers, the team offers a range of interventions and approaches aimed at emphasising hope and optimism, and developing personal strengths to help achieve recovery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The remit brings us into contact with patients with a range of mental health, social, psychological and situational difficulties from the diverse population of Derbyshire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a service we are looking for an individual with leadership experience, someone who can work at pace to continue to support the developments of the service as it grows.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Crisis services are currently receiving considerable investment, and with this investment comes an emphasis to provide an effective and responsive service providing safe care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an individual who shows compassion and who is engaging and focussed on service user and carer satisfaction, as well as someone who is able to support a team through challenges and change.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As Service Manager you will also be working alongside the Band 7 Clinical Lead in the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will also include taking a lead and participating in monitoring the service at defined intervals, and assisting in the making of recommendations regarding this team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be involved and at times provide training, presentations and seminars to staff to promote the service developments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will provide supervision and support to the CORE team and support the Area Service Manager in the on-going development of the service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will also work with and be supported by the Area Service Manager and Nurse Consultant, as well as from colleagues across the Assessment Services line.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The assessment services team include crisis services in South Derbyshire, North Derbyshire and High Peak, Liaison Teams based in the Emergency Departments in Chesterfield and Derby, as well as our newer developing service the Mental health helpline/ Mental Health Triage and the 136.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact Fiona White, Area Service Manager, on 01246 512563 or &lt;em&gt;fiona.white21@nhs.net&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are committed to equal opportunities and improving the working lives of all our staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We will consider applications to work flexibly.&lt;/p&gt;
